# __CONTAINER_NAME__

Containerized agent built on the Reusable Agent Framework.

## Architecture

This container follows the layered architecture described in the confluence
"Reusable Agent Components - Foundation":

- `src/domain/` — Layer 1: agent-specific entities and execution state
- `src/application/` — Layer 2: workflow nodes, tools, callbacks
- `src/composition/` — Layer 5: composition root that wires dependencies
- `src/services/` — LLM and vault clients (thin wrappers over shared packages)
- `src/config/` — agent configuration (populated by `setup-agent-infra`)
- `src/database/` — MongoDB adapters (populated by `setup-agent-infra`)
- `src/vectorstore/` — Weaviate adapters (populated by `setup-agent-infra`)
- `src/utils/` — global state + helpers (populated by `setup-agent-infra`)
- `src/models/` — DTOs: `ExecutionRequest`, `ExecutionResult`
- `src/exceptions/` — custom exception hierarchy per confluence error-handling strategy

## Development

```sh
make install
make format
make lint
```

## Running

```sh
python src/main.py
```
